1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,733
- Olive.
- Emma!

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,500
- Ma'am!
- Olive.

3
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:16,667
I know you're here.
So come out now!

4
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:20,867
Brace yourself once I find out
you're in cahoots with them.

5
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:23,967
You know what? You look alike.

6
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:25,167
You can pass as mother
and daughter.

7
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,733
Flor called me.

8
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,967
She gave me your diary
so we should meet.

9
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,933
My mom might see me.

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,400
Promise, I'll be careful.

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,267
- Mommy, don't! Please!
- Come on, Mookie.

12
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,700
- Let's go home.
- Please stop! That's enough!

13
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,733
Leave her to me.

14
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,533
Over my dead body!

15
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,667
- Move! Mookie!
- I'll take care of her!

16
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,633
I'm in pain because I left her.

17
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,700
I'll get even with them!

18
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,233
I'll take revenge!

19
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,967
I really wish
you were my family.

20
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:54,300
And you were my mom.

21
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:35,467
Mommy Emma.

22
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:45,233
Maybe our paths crossed because
they know you'll protect me.

23
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:50,067
You really are so different
from my mom.

24
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,100
Because...

25
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,400
my mom doesn't seem...

26
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,100
to treat me as her daughter.

27
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,133
She doesn't seem to love me.

28
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:05,667
But you don't treat me
as a stranger.

29
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,300
You know...

30
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:12,100
anyone...

31
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:14,933
will get fond of you.

32
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,667
Look at my mom.

33
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:22,200
At first, she wasn't comfortable
with you staying here.

34
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:26,233
But now, you've melted
her heart.

35
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:28,400
Because you're a kind kid.

36
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:32,033
You're kinder.

37
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:38,367
You made me happy
the first time we met, remember?

38
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:43,667
And we love the same lullabies.

39
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:50,667
You know what, Mom?
I feel like I'm your daughter.

40
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,833
I feel like you're my mother.

41
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,800
I really wish you were my mom.

42
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:02,400
Oh, Dear.

43
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:03,600
Come here.

44
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:11,433
Whether I'm your mom or not,
I'll always be here for you.

45
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,967
I'll take care of you.

46
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:17,300
That's a promise.

47
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:35,467
I'm sure Ma'am Olive
won't leave us alone.

48
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:38,167
But Mookie doesn't want me
to report to the police.

49
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:41,233
I don't understand that kid.
She's so kind.

50
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:44,833
She doesn't want her mom
to pay for what she did to her.

51
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:48,033
Mom, you can't blame her.

52
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:49,600
That's still her mother.

53
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,167
I know.

54
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:52,600
You are right.

55
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,867
That's why I feel more bad
for that kid,

56
00:03:55,967 --> 00:03:59,067
especially since Olive
is mentally ill.

57
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:02,133
It's dangerous for her
to go back.

58
00:04:02,633 --> 00:04:07,500
We don't know what else her
crazy mother can do to her.

59
00:04:07,567 --> 00:04:10,867
By the way,
Bukoy and I met earlier.

60
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:13,600
He'll go with me to the DSWD.

61
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:14,867
But I'll be right back

62
00:04:14,933 --> 00:04:18,000
so we can celebrate because
it's your birthday tomorrow.

63
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,000
Oh, my!

64
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:21,100
Yes, Mom.
It's her birthday tomorrow.

65
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:25,600
With all that's happening,
I forgot it's your birthday.

66
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,967
I'm sorry, Dear.

67
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:30,367
But we have to have even
a simple celebration.

68
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:31,900
Yes, it's just a simple
celebration.

69
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:34,967
No, Mom. We don't have to.
It doesn't matter anymore.

70
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:37,833
What matters is for me
to find my daughter,

71
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,333
and to keep Mookie safe.

72
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,333
That would be the best gift for
me.

73
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:44,100
And I know that, someday,

74
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:49,233
I have to let go of Mookie
because I have no right to her.

75
00:04:50,933 --> 00:04:59,667
But I'm sure I'll get hurt
because I treat her as my own.

76
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:04,100
Me, too, Ems.

77
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,400
I've been like a father
to Mookie.

78
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,433
I feel like...

79
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,367
Kayla's with us.

80
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:17,733
Wherever Kayla is, I hope

81
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:23,033
she has someone like us
who truly cares for her.

82
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:37,167
Flor?

83
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:40,567
I was planning to leave
because I was scared

84
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,867
of what Ma'am Olive could do.

85
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:47,267
But I saw Manang Sefa
at the bus station.

86
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:47,967
Sefa?

87
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:50,133
Who's Sefa?

88
00:05:51,167 --> 00:05:53,333
Ma'am Olive's former helper.

89
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,567
She worked there before me.

90
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:58,200
She knows a lot of information

91
00:05:58,267 --> 00:06:01,733
about Mookie and Ma'am Olive
that might help you.

92
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:10,300
Do you mean you were working
for Olive

93
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,967
even before Mookie was born?

94
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:14,133
Yes.

95
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,500
I used to be Ma'am Olive's
caretaker

96
00:06:16,567 --> 00:06:18,700
in her house in Manila.

97
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:20,433
I stayed there often.

98
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:27,767
But my husband wanted me to stop
working, so I resigned.

99
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:31,400
Not long after,
Ma'am Olive called me

100
00:06:31,467 --> 00:06:33,267
and asked for a helper.

101
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:35,833
And I recommended Flor.

102
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:40,500
Sefa and I couldn't talk
back then

103
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,767
because she went home
to the province.

104
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:48,600
Ma'am Olive
became more irritable.

105
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,733
I couldn't stand
her attitude anymore.

106
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:54,933
Especially when her child died.

107
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,800
Olive lost a child?

108
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:30,533
Olive...

109
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:34,633
you haven't gone out
of your room for days now.

110
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:36,400
You also don't seem to eat.

111
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:42,667
You know, you were exactly like
this when Maria Angela died.

112
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:45,133
Please. Don't neglect yourself.

113
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:49,800
Dead?

114
00:07:53,233 --> 00:07:55,133
Angela isn't dead!

115
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:57,867
My child isn't dead!

116
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,400
She's taken away from me.

117
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,867
Emma took her away.

118
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:09,367
And I won't lose my child
that way!

119
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:12,633
I struggled so hard
when I gave birth to her.

120
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:15,333
Gave birth?

121
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:17,100
Yes!

122
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,333
Weren't you there, Astrid?

123
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,867
You were there
when I was pregnant

124
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:24,700
and gave birth to Angela.

125
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,167
So she's mine.

126
00:08:29,633 --> 00:08:31,167
Angela is only mine!

127
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:34,733
And I'll do everything
in my power...

128
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,067
to take her back.

129
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,300
Why didn't I know about that?

130
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:52,400
It's not my habit to talk about
my former employers' lives.

131
00:08:52,467 --> 00:08:54,300
But you said the information
I know

132
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:59,667
might help to file a case
against Ma'am Olive.

133
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:03,100
If she lost a child,

134
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,400
when did she give birth
to Mookie?

135
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:06,400
I don't know.

136
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:11,167
All I know is Ma'am Olive
didn't marry.

137
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:14,000
The man who got her pregnant
left her.

138
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:17,033
Maria Angela's dad.

139
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,567
Maria Angela?

140
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,167
Wait.

141
00:09:20,233 --> 00:09:23,100
That's also Mookie's name.

142
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:30,467
So, she named Mookie
after her dead child?

143
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:36,133
So, she named Mookie
after her dead child?

144
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:37,700
I don't know.

145
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:44,567
When I visited someone I knew in
the village, I saw Ma'am Olive.

146
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:47,167
I just dropped by
to see how you're doing.

147
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:49,800
You're lucky you're still
working here.

148
00:09:52,367 --> 00:09:53,700
The dog?

149
00:09:53,767 --> 00:09:55,600
Did you see a dog?

150
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,133
Look at the dog.

151
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,600
Arf! Arf!

152
00:09:58,667 --> 00:09:59,600
Ma'am Olive?

153
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,267
Ma'am Olive had another child?

154
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:03,467
You like that?

155
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,167
What does the bird say?

156
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:11,900
My friend also said
they didn't see her marry.

157
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,600
She just suddenly had a child.

158
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,333
Don't you know that, Flor?

159
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:21,767
No, Mookie was already there
when I came.

160
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:24,100
I don't know anything
about Ma'am Olive's past.

161
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,200
Don't you think...

162
00:10:28,300 --> 00:10:29,867
she just adopted Mookie?

163
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:54,800
- Surprise!
- Surprise!

164
00:10:55,267 --> 00:11:04,133
- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you!

165
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:09,633
Happy birthday,
happy birthday!

166
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:16,600
- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you!

167
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:19,067
Wait. Make a wish first.

168
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:26,400
Dear God, thank you
for allowing me to live.

169
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:30,667
I won't wish for anything
for my birthday...

170
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,700
other than finding Kayla.

171
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:43,167
- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you!

172
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:46,800
- One more!
- Happy birthday to you!

173
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:50,967
Oh, Dear!

174
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:54,433
This is so touching.

175
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,933
But isn't this too much?

176
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,033
We're already staying here, and
you still prepared food for me.

177
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:03,033
Emma, forget about that.

178
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:06,600
Who else will support each other
if not us, neighbors? Right?

179
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,633
Right!

180
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:09,733
Thank you.

181
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,700
Do you know whose idea this is?

182
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:13,267
It's that kid's idea.

183
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:16,467
She wants you to be happy
on your birthday.

184
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:23,933
And we won in Big Two, so we
contributed money for the food.

185
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:26,667
Thank you. Thank you.

186
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,633
Happy birthday, Dear.

187
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:31,200
And Mookie has a surprise.

188
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,833
You have a surprise?

189
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,633
- Yes, Mom.
- Sit down.

190
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,267
- Come on.
- Over here.

191
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,133
This is for you, Mom.

192
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:48,067
Hush now, dear

193
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:52,433
Come here

194
00:12:52,500 --> 00:13:00,667
Sleep along with the stars

195
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:04,433
I'll stay with you

196
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:08,100
I won't hurt you

197
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:15,867
You'll always be safe with me

198
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:22,833
And I promise you
I will forever guide you

199
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:27,633
My friend said they never saw
her getting married.

200
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:30,167
She just suddenly had a child.

201
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:34,467
Mookie was already there
when I came.

202
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:38,067
Come here

203
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,000
Don't you think...

204
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,300
she just adopted Mookie?

205
00:13:46,933 --> 00:13:49,200
- Wow!
- Nice!

206
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:51,033
What a beautiful voice!
Lucky you!

207
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:05,000
Olive, what are you doing?

208
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:08,100
I'm going live on social media.

209
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,967
What? Why?

210
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:13,767
I'm getting impatient
with the police.

211
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,333
I'll do it my way.

212
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:20,033
Because I won't let Mookie
completely disappear in my life.

213
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,267
Thank you, Dear.

214
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:33,600
Happy birthday, Mom!

215
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,233
You sing very well.

216
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:41,200
That's for you, Mom.

217
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:47,933
Well, Miss Ligaya told me that
Baby Kayla might still be alive.

218
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,200
But someone took her.

219
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,733
Don't worry, Mom.

220
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,900
I'll pray that you find
your daughter.

221
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:04,367
And I'll introduce you to Kayla
once I find her.

222
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:05,833
I'm sure, Mom...

223
00:15:06,867 --> 00:15:09,033
she's a good person like you.

224
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:11,733
And we'll be best of friends.

225
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:15,133
Not just best friends.

226
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:18,333
I'll tell her to treat you
as a sister

227
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:21,100
because you're a good kid,
Mookie.

228
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:25,433
That's not impossible to happen.

229
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,867
Thank you.

230
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:32,700
I'm happy you're here
even though Kayla's not.

231
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,767
- Happy birthday, Mom!
- Thank you.

232
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,800
And because of that...

233
00:15:41,867 --> 00:15:43,533
Time to eat!

234
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:47,267
- Yes. You are so...
- It's your birthday.

235
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:50,633
Let's go! Let's eat, come on!
This is good!

236
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,700
Don't spoil the fun.
It's your daughter's birthday.

237
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:54,833
Let's go. Come on, come on,
birthday girl. Hurry!

238
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,033
Happy birthday! Happy birthday!

239
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,667
The food looks delicious.

240
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:02,367
- Here.
- Let's go. This is the...

241
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:09,233
I'll go with you
to the DSWD after this, Danilo.

242
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:11,300
Thank you, Bukoy.

243
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:14,700
I really hope we can find
the woman who took my child.

244
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:17,800
So we can confirm
if Baby Kayla's still alive.

245
00:16:19,067 --> 00:16:21,467
And then we've had this problem
with Mookie.

246
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:24,400
I feel sorry for Emma.

247
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:27,267
It's her birthday today.

248
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:33,500
Hey!

249
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:34,633
- Oh, no. I wonder who kidnapped
- My daughter has been

250
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,500
- this woman's child.
 - missing for days now.

251
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,267
Yes. I'm wondering, too.

252
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,567
So you've seen it, too?

253
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:43,667
I don't know where to find her.

254
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:46,733
Maybe she's already
so scared right now.

255
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:50,133
The kidnappers might be
doing something bad to her.

256
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:55,967
I'm begging you.

257
00:16:56,033 --> 00:16:57,867
Please help me.

258
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,900
Help me bring her back home.

259
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:05,700
She's too young
to get separated from me.

260
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,367
And look.

261
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:12,833
She is also very sick.

262
00:17:16,133 --> 00:17:20,633
And don't worry,
because I won't waste your help.

263
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:24,633
I will offer
a one million peso reward

264
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:27,200
to whoever finds my daughter.

265
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:31,900
And who can tell
where her kidnappers are.

266
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,233
What?

267
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:36,433
Do you mean Mookie
is only Olive's adopted child?

268
00:17:37,567 --> 00:17:38,700
Mom, that's what I think.

269
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:41,300
And that explains why
she treats Mookie like that.

270
00:17:41,367 --> 00:17:43,333
If that's the case,
where did she come from?

271
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,700
Who are her parents?

272
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,033
- Oh. Oh, sorry, sorry, sorry.
- Oh. Sorry, sorry, Mookie.

273
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,133
- I'm sorry.
- Mookie?

274
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,500
- Are you hurt?
- Mookie?

275
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:54,767
Oh.

276
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:55,867
- Sit down first.
- Emma, we were just playing.

277
00:17:55,933 --> 00:17:57,300
- Yes, we were just...
- What happened?

278
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:59,333
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry. Yes.

279
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:02,233
- Oh my God.
- Please get the medicine.

280
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:03,700
I'll get the first-aid kit.

281
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:06,133
- Mom, I'm okay.
- Let me see.

282
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,867
Let me see, let me see.

283
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:10,133
Here, here. Here you go.

284
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:10,833
Please give it to me.

285
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:15,233
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

286
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:16,367
Are you okay, Dear?

287
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:19,900
Yes. I'm fine, Mom. Don't worry.

288
00:18:19,967 --> 00:18:22,100
Mom, can you hand me
the medicine?

289
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,100
Does it still hurt?

290
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,633
Let's wipe this out first.

291
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:29,167
All right.

292
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:32,500
Okay. I'll get going.

293
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:33,933
Bro, wait.

294
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,700
That woman looks familiar to me.

295
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:37,633
Olive?

296
00:18:43,033 --> 00:18:45,733
Danilo! Danilo!

297
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,100
Hey, Miss!
Where are you taking Kayla?

298
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:50,133
Danilo!

299
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:55,600
I wonder who she is.

300
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,500
Is she Danilo's relative?

301
00:18:57,567 --> 00:18:59,000
Miss, you dropped this!

302
00:18:59,067 --> 00:19:02,467
Miss! Miss, you dropped this!
Miss!

303
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:07,000
Bro, remember the day
we had a landslide?

304
00:19:08,233 --> 00:19:09,600
She's that woman.

305
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:11,933
She's the one
who took your child.

306
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,300
What?

307
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:14,267
Olive?

308
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:30,167
Mom?

309
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:34,700
Why?

310
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:35,533
Dear?

311
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,333
Why?

312
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,033
Bukoy, I know her.

313
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,567
Is she the one
who took our child?

314
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:02,133
Yes, I'm sure of it.

315
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:04,367
Aren't you mistaken?

316
00:20:04,433 --> 00:20:06,467
Who's the woman
we followed at the airport?

317
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:07,933
I don't know.

318
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,767
Maybe she's back.

319
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,800
I can't be mistaken, Bro.

320
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:13,700
I won't forget that face.

321
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:15,000
Because we encountered
each other.

322
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:20,067
Emma must know about this.
Let's go!

323
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,200
Dear?

324
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:26,967
Why are you crying, Mom?

325
00:20:28,133 --> 00:20:30,000
Mom, I'm really okay.

326
00:20:30,067 --> 00:20:31,700
- Emma.
- Don't worry.

327
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:32,333
Oh.

328
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:34,633
Here.

329
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,767
Here's the medicine.

330
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:39,533
Hey, Emma.

331
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:40,933
What's going on with you?

332
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:44,233
Here's the medicine
you asked me to get.

333
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,433
What happened?

334
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,800
I don't know, either.

335
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,567
Mom, I'm really okay. I promise.

336
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:52,433
Emma!

337
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,933
- Emma!
- Emma!

338
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,833
Olive is live on social media.

339
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,433
- Look at the picture
- Look.

340
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,700
of this woman.

341
00:20:57,767 --> 00:21:02,433
She's Emma Joseco,
our former laundress.

342
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,700
And she kidnapped my child!

343
00:21:07,267 --> 00:21:12,667
So, please, remember this face.

344
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:15,667
This woman is a kidnapper!

345
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:19,133
And she mercilessly
took my daughter!

346
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,833
So if you see her...

347
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:23,867
report her to the police!

348
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:27,500
Spread this video.
Share it. I'm begging you.

349
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:30,500
And if you need to arrest her,
do so!

350
00:21:30,567 --> 00:21:32,967
That woman is unbelievable!

351
00:21:33,033 --> 00:21:35,467
Emma, she's telling everyone
you're a kidnapper.

352
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:36,967
Oh!

353
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,067
What do we do?

354
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:41,833
The police might arrest
Mommy Emma again.

355
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,267
Oh, boy, it'll put
Emma in danger,

356
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:45,733
especially since
there's a reward.

357
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,033
That's possible.

358
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:49,433
The people might attack her
for money.

359
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,600
Or the police can arrest her.

360
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:54,133
Emma.

361
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,700
What do we do?

362
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:02,700
Can Mookie and I talk first?

363
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,700
- Let's go.
- She said they'll talk.

364
00:22:07,767 --> 00:22:09,400
BFF, come on.
They'll have a talk.

365
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:10,967
- Let's go.
- Me, too?

366
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:13,333
- Yes! let them.
- Let them talk.

367
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,700
What's wrong with you?

368
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:24,767
I'm not done yet!
Why did you stop it?

369
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,700
Olive, enough!

370
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:29,167
You'll only harm yourself!

371
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:32,300
Well, this is the only way
to get Mookie back!

372
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:35,033
Olive, stop.

373
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,100
Reporting it to the police
is already risky,

374
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:38,333
what more doing a live stream.

375
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,967
Once Emma files a child abuse
case against you,

376
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:44,500
and the people see this,
this might go viral.

377
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:45,867
You're not just going to jail.

378
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,900
The whole world
will also talk about you.

379
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:49,133
I don't care!

380
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:55,000
What's important to me right now
is to get Mookie back from Emma.

381
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:58,567
Dear...

382
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:01,900
Have you had that birthmark
on your leg for a long time?

383
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:02,933
Yes, Mom.

384
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:07,800
I've had it since I was born.

385
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,700
Why did you ask?

386
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:15,500
I'm not sure
if what I feel is right.

387
00:23:15,567 --> 00:23:20,567
Or if what I'm thinking is
right, but I have a feeling.

388
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:23,067
You have a feeling that?

389
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:27,867
Mookie, I'm not sure if I should
tell you what I feel right now.

390
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:37,667
If you will not meet with me,

391
00:23:37,733 --> 00:23:40,567
I will tell the police
where your mommy Emma is

392
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:43,067
if you don't meet me.

393
00:23:43,133 --> 00:23:45,500
Okay, I'll meet with you.

394
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:46,800
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

395
00:23:46,867 --> 00:23:47,700
Did you see her?

396
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:52,733
We saw Mookie
in Gabo's tricycle!

397
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,667
Mookie?

398
00:23:56,233 --> 00:23:57,233
Mommy.

399
00:23:57,300 --> 00:24:00,067
The picture that Olive
showed looks like you.

400
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:01,233
It's you, right?

401
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:02,700
You're the kidnapper!

402
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:04,400
I'm not her,
I'm not a kidnapper!

403
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:08,300
Mookie, just do everything
I want, and we'll be okay.

404
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:10,133
- No...
- Just like the old times, okay?

405
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:12,300
- I don't want to, Mommy!
- Mookie!

406
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:14,033
- Miss Ligaya, please help me!
- Olive!

407
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:14,967
Help!

408
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:16,633
Where are you taking Mookie?

409
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:18,367
Go get the car, hurry!

410
00:24:18,433 --> 00:24:19,700
Go ahead! Come near us!

411
00:24:19,767 --> 00:24:20,300
Go on!

412
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:23,100
Emma!
